//! # Widget Trait
//!
//! The [`Widget`] trait defines how components render themselves.
//!
//! ## Frame vs Buffer
//!
//! Widgets receive a [`Frame`] which provides:
//! - **buffer** - Cell grid for drawing (same as legacy Buffer API)
//! - **hit_grid** - Optional mouse click region registration
//! - **cursor_position** - Cursor placement for input widgets
//! - **degradation** - Performance budget adaptation level
//!
//! ## Migration from Buffer API
//!
//! Most widgets only need buffer access:
//! ```rust
//! fn render(&self, area: Rect, frame: &mut Frame) {
//!     let buf = &mut frame.buffer;
//!     // ... use buf as before
//! }
//! ```
